Credo (CRDO) advances next as DustPhotonics adds ready optics to its active cable and ZeroFlap lineup. This holds because hyperscalers now prioritize in‑rack to between‑rack optical links for faster AI cluster buildouts. Today’s strong after‑hours pop reflects the headline, while multi‑quarter design wins and module ramps remain only partly shown in price action this week. DSPs and optical modules shift from nice‑to‑have to must‑have as rack bandwidth climbs. Peer precedence from Marvell’s Celestial AI deal supports a rerate window. Memory‑to‑compute bandwidth needs keep optics at the center for AI rollouts."}}}, "rest_id": "2043814584222658950", "source": "<a href="https://mobile.twitter.com" rel="nofollow">Twitter Web App</a>", "unmention_data": {}, "views": {"count": "169", "state": "EnabledWithCount"}}

